      "Medical evaluation performed"
    ],
    "summary": "On 08-June-2014, during mobilization of the Blake 1505 rig onto ANKOR Energy's VR-379A facility, a cargo basket being lifted by the platform crane caught on a handrail on the rig floor. The handrail was pulled from its support sockets and fell 37 feet 7 inches to the top deck, striking a construction worker operating an air tugger. The worker sustained contusions to the neck and shoulder areas and was evacuated for medical evaluation.",
